column2:
Like many multiplayer games that have been out there for a few years, it's plagued with cheaters (who often only get 1 day bans [i][b]if[/b][/i] they get caught) and max level players who play this game so much, they look like cheaters, which is a huge problem because matchmaking is basically nonexistent, so you'll often be paired against those two, even if you play casual mode (which you can only play 3 times a day btw). 

That brings it to the other problem that is, the devs made this game free in order to attract new players, but did very little to make sure they have a decent experience, so that they stick around. Instead, they focus on dumping even more expensive gun skins and goofy outfits into the game to milk their ever decreasing playerbase.

Other issues include:

- no ability to choose which map you wanna play on, they're always randomly picked save for casual mode which is always on Erangel (the classic, first map);

- poor weapon balancing leading to players mostly only ever using the "meta" weapons; 

- exploitable game mechanics that give experienced players an unfair edge such as spamming leaning and crouching to avoid headshots; 

- terrible sound mixing (gunshots are too loud while footsteps are too low in comparison); 

- lack of different modes for ranked matches, you can only pick between 4-man-squad and solo-vs-squads both on first person view mode only (this is made worse by the fact ranked matches are locked behind a paywall);

- inconsistent damage model that favours headshots too much;

Don't be like me and waste your time trying to learn this game and be good at it, it's not gonna happen and it's frankly not worth it. It's only sometimes fun if you're playing this with friends on casual mode (12 players,  the rest are bots) and happen to be lucky enough to get a decent match without having to deal with too many max level try-hards / cheaters, otherwise you're better off playing something else unless you have no self-love. This might have been the best BR game at one point, but it's clear its days of glory are long gone and it's not looking like it's making a comeback.

